u
\int_{-1}^{1} \frac{dx}{4 + x^2}.
\tan u = \frac{x}{2},
\tan u = x/2
a = 2
\int \frac{dx}{x^2 + a^2} = \frac{1}{a}\tan^{-1}\left(\frac{x}{a}\right) + C
\tan u = x/a
x = a\tan u
dx/du = a \sec^2 u
u = \tan^{-1}(x/a)
1 + \tan^2 u = \sec^2 u.
\int \frac{dx}{x^2 + a^2} = \int \frac{a \sec^2 u}{a^2(1 + \tan^2 u)} du = \int \frac{du}{a} = \frac{1}{a}\tan^{-1}\left(\frac{x}{a}\right) + C.
